CVE.summary: Multiple SQL injection vulnerabilities in Enthrallweb eHomes allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary SQL commands via the (1) cid parameter to (a) dircat.asp; the (2) sid parameter to (b) dirSub.asp; the (3) TYPE_ID parameter to (c) types.asp; the (4) AD_ID parameter to (d) homeDetail.asp; the (5) cat parameter to (e) result.asp; the (6) compare, (7) clear, and (8) adID parameters to (f) compareHomes.asp; and the (9) aminprice, (10) amaxprice, and (11) abedrooms parameters to (g) result.asp.
